## Example Usage

**User says:** "Turn this SAM3 paper into a blog post"

**Workflow:**
1. Convert SAM3 PDF to markdown using markdownify MCP
2. Read the converted markdown content
3. Generate comprehensive 2000-word blog article following the writing instructions
4. Render PDF pages as images using pypdfium2/PyMuPDF
5. Use AI vision analysis (`mcp__4_5v_mcp__analyze_image`) to identify figures/tables on each page
6. Extract identified visual regions and save to `pdf/PaperLog/figures/`
7. Update image references in blog to use `![](figures/filename.png)`
8. Remove full page image references
9. Save to `pdf/PaperLog/SAM3_的技术革命：统一视觉模型如何重塑监控视频理解.md`

## Output Format

The final output should be a well-structured markdown file containing:
- Compelling Chinese headline
- 7 structured sections with flowing prose (~2000 words total)
- Introduction (200-300 words)
- Background & Context (250-350 words)
- Core Methodology (400-500 words)
- Key Findings & Results (400-500 words)
- Implications & Applications (250-350 words)
- Conclusion (150-200 words)
- Minimal bullet points (max 1-2 short lists)
- Actual extracted figures/tables with `![](figures/filename.png)` paths
- Substantive, specific content throughout
